      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it feels deeper than just visual poetry. like, when i look at specific gaps in the early chapters, it's not just \"silence\"... it's more like they're hiding actual data or messages that the text is trying to mask. it's like the real narrative is tucked into the voids. do u think it's possible for a text to have a secondary, hidden layer of information that's transmitted through the spacing instead of the letters?",
